CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 7, 1953, pg. 5, reads: "Slated to Go - The forty units of veterans' housing at Morgan Street and Webster Avenue are slated for early demolition as part of the Pittsburgh Housing Authority program to end the use of the converted Army barracks as temporary housing. These old barracks were originally scheduled to be used for three years.  They are now in their eighth year of occupancy. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Two story clapboard veterans housing (formerly Army barracks) on Webster Avenue at Morgan Street, with women walking on sidewalk on left, and car parked on right, Hill District
